b97a5ce0-c8d1-4916-abfe-d377da8a91bb.text:
Classical Waterfall Model The classical waterfall model is a sequential software development process
where progress flows in one direction: requirements fi design fi implementation fi testing fi
deployment fi maintenance. Key Characteristics: - Linear, phase-based approach -
Documentation-heavy - No feedback loops between phases - Best suited for well-understood, stable
requirements Common Uses: - Military systems - Manufacturing - Large enterprise systems with fixed
requirements
